-- China to Step Up Regulation of Artifacts Market, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2012-03-28T18:16:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/china-to-step-up-regulation-of-artifacts-market-xinhua-reports.html
China plans to intensify regulation
and management of the “chaotic” cultural-artifacts market,
Xinhua News Agency said, citing Li Yaoshen, an official at the
State Administration of Cultural Heritage.  The government agency will set up a sytem to manage and
regulate certificates of authenticity and promulgate more
specific rules on the conduct of auctions of relics, the
official news service reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  